window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b><i>One deal, one mistake, one impossible choice.</i></b></p><p></p><p>All I ever wanted was to escape the world of wolves - not be forced into a loveless marriage with Ashton, the Alpha of Nightclaw, and be tied down forever.</p><p></p><p>But being the only human in a pack of wolves, my desires mattered little.</p><p></p><p>Desperate to stop the wedding, I make a mistake — one that makes Ashton realize how much we both despise this mating.</p><p></p><p>So he offers me a deal: marry him, give him an heir, and then I can walk away, leaving Nightclaw and him behind forever.</p><p></p><p>I take the deal, knowing it is my only way out, believing I can walk away unscathed.</p><p></p><p><b><i>When love is the last thing you expect, it becomes the only thing you need.</i></b></p><p></p><p>We tie the knot, and he claims me as his Luna.</p><p></p><p>But as I get to know him, I do the one thing I swore I wouldn’t - I fall in love with the Alpha.</p><p></p><p>The man who had vowed to let me go now held my heart in his hands.</p><p></p><p><b><i>He was bound to me by duty, but he claimed my heart by choice.</i></b></p><p></p><p>Love does not follow rules, and neither do the secrets lurking in the shadows.</p><p></p><p>When Ashton’s buried secrets resurface, shattering my heart, I am left grappling with the truth of our relationship.</p><p></p><p>His haunting past — the truth about his true mate — unveils thorns that wrap around my heart.</p><p></p><p>Had Ashton ever truly loved me, or had the lines between love and hatred blurred for me alone?</p><p></p><p><b><i>Love was never part of the deal, but neither was betrayal.</i></b></p><p></p><p>As the ghosts of the past threaten to tear us apart, a startling revelation shakes my core.</p><p></p><p>I am pregnant with the Alpha’s child.</p><p></p><p><b><i>He was supposed to be a means to an end, but he became my everything.</i></b></p><p></p><p>Then the girls in the pack begin disappearing, and a sinister threat comes to light.</p><p></p><p>With enemies closing in and betrayal lurking around every corner, the pack’s survival is on the line, and I find myself right in the middle of it all.</p><p></p><p><b><i>When you fall for the Alpha, there’s no running from the wolves.</i></b></p><p></p><p><b>~~~*~~~</b></p><p></p><p><b>Happily ever after (HEA).</b></p><p><b>Standalone novel.</b></p><p><b>Tropes: Alpha's rejected mate, secret baby, grovel romance, fated mates, second chance love, human mate, arranged marriage, contract marriage, enemies to lovers.</b></p>"; 
